            <div id="primary-content">
              <a name="48612"></a><h1>Flexible working</h1>






<!--start Further Content-->
<a name="d.en.48619"></a>
<h2>Guidance for departmental administrators </h2>
<div  class="teaser"></div>
<p>Flexible working can include a wide variety of working practices. A flexible working arrangement can be any working pattern other than the normal working pattern in your department. Examples could include:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/personnel/during/hours/ptw_regs/">part-time working</a>;</li>
<li>compressed hours (for example, working full weekly hours over four rather than five days);</li>
<li>job-sharing;</li>
<li>staggered hours;</li>
<li>term-time only working, or</li>
<li><a href="http://www.admin.ox.ac.uk/personnel/during/flexible/homeworking/">working from home</a> ("teleworking")</li>
</ul>
<p>There is also provision for <a href="/personnel/end/retirement/flexretire/">flexible retirement</a>.&nbsp; A scheme allowing, with University approval, a mixture of retirement and continuity at work.</p>
<!-- navigation object : Gl Back to Top -->
<!--end Further Content-->
<!--start Further Content-->
<a name="d.en.48670"></a>

